          <div class="popcontent" id="popcnt_1">
                    <strong>Examples:</strong> On Campus, In Auditoriums <br>
                    <strong>Presentation:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Dress in comfortable Formals or Business Casuals.</li>
                            <li>Maintain a calm and confident demeanor.</li>
                            <li>Wear clean, polished, formal shoes.</li>
                            <li>Ensure fresh breath and body odor.</li>
                            <li>Avoid smoking or chewing gum. It can be a big put-off for the candidate.</li>
                            <li>Wear the Smile!</li>
                        </ul>
                    <strong>Environment:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Ensure that your desk is clutter free.</li>
                            <li>Assign a comfortable place for candidates.</li>
                            <li>Ensure that environment is noise-free. </li>
                            <li>Keep a list of all candidates handy.</li>
                            <li>Turn off your mobiles. It can be very distracting.</li>
                        </ul>           
                    <div style="margin-left: 675px; margin-top:-317px;"><img src="../shared/images/tab2_1.png" /></div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="popcontent" id="popcnt_2">
                    <strong>Examples</strong>: Telephonic, Skype Audio<br>
                    <strong>Presentation:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Although not a face-to-face interview, it is a good practice to dress professionally<br>for confidence and clarity.</li>
                            <li>Smile! It projects a positive tone in your voice and image. </li>
                        </ul>
                    <strong>Environment:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Check quality of audio systems, speakers or the telephone depending the mode used.</li>
                            <li>Be in a quiet place alone. Avoid noisy open areas.</li>
                            <li>Turn off the radio, television or any other background noise.</li>
                            <li>Maintain a clutter free area. </li>
                            <li>Keep a pen and paper handy to take notes.</li>
                        </ul>           
                    <div style="margin-left: 643px; margin-top:-105px;"><img src="../shared/images/tab2_2.png" /></div>
                </div>
                
                
                <div class="popcontent" id="popcnt_3">
                    <strong>Examples</strong>: Video conferencing, Skype, Google Hangouts, FaceTime<br>
                    <strong>Presentation:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Dress in comfortable Formals or Business Casuals.</li>
                            <li>Maintain a calm and confident demeanor.</li>
                            <li>Avoid smoking or chewing gum. It can be a big put-off for the candidate.</li>
                            <li>Wear the <strong>Smile</strong>! Helps connect with the candidate.</li>
                        </ul>
                    <strong>Environment:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Get familiar with the platform or mode you are using.</li>
                            <li>Ensure that your desk is clutter free.</li>
                            <li>Reach at least 10 minutes ahead of time and test all equipment. </li>
                            <li>Keep only relevant paper work with you for reference.</li>
                            <li>Ensure that environment is noise-free.</li>
                        </ul>           
